Take a break from your Tuesday and head to the beach to meet our 3rd Grade Teacher, Ms. Deborah Graves!

Ms. Graves has been instrumental in ensuring our students meet 3rd Grade Reading Guarantee standards. In fact, 100% of Eagle Elementary's students have passed the 3rd Grade Reading Guarantee 3 years in a row!

Thank you Ms. Graves!

To read more about Ohio's 3rd Grade Reading guarantee, click here:
http://education.ohio.gov/Topics/Learning-in-Ohio/Literacy/Third-Grade-Reading-Guarantee

We are a tuition-free charter school in Akron, OH serving low income families.
Due to safety concerns, we had to shut down our playground this fall which has left our students without their most treasured recess pastime.

We need your help to raise $5,000 to replace mulch, repair damages, and hire labor to preform repairs.

Please help us get our playgound back up and running so our students can enjoy recess!

post_text:
The school year is off to a great start! Students participate in daily morning meetings where they are explicitly taught calming strategies. As a class they practice these strategies throughout the day. They have also begun to use a variety of "tools" to help them stay focused. As you can see in the pictures students are using fidgets, chair bands, wiggle disks, quiet zones, and breathing balls to help them self regulate.
Every student learns differently and every student has unique learning style needs. For some, they spend all their time sitting upright and still that their ability to gain new information is dramatically impacted. As teachers, it is our job to not only provide students with tools, but to also teach them to become self aware and advocate for their learning needs.
Students will continue to practice how to use these tools effectively and appropriately in the classroom. Our goal is to teach students life skills that will translate outside our classroom walls.

Due to the current and expected frigid temperatures in the area. School has been CLOSED Wednesday Jan. 30th- Thursday 31st.

Please do not leave children unattended outside for any period of time.

Wear appropriate outdoor clothing: layers of light, warm clothing; windproof coat, mittens; hats; scarves; and waterproof boots.

Be safe and stay warm!

post_text:
Please make sure your children are dressed appropriately for these cold days. Hats, boots, snow pants, warm jackets, layers, scarves, and gloves or mittens are essential for students to safely be outside for any period of time.

It is important that children not be allowed to leave the house with exposed skin (ears, hands, legs, etc.), as this increases the chance of frostbite in cold weather. ‚òÉÔ∏è‚òÉÔ∏è‚òÉÔ∏è
